snippet: The call by the formerly outlawed Islamist group moved Egypt one step closer to a long-anticipated confrontation between the ruling generals and the Islamist-dominated Parliament.
abstract: Muslim Brotherhood demands that Egypt’s military rulers cede control of the government, stepping closer to a long-anticipated confrontation between the ruling generals and the Islamist-dominated Parliament; group appears to be effectively agreeing with street protesters and liberals on need for military to leave power at a time when it appears overwhelmed by domestic and foreign crises.
lead_paragraph: The call by the formerly outlawed Islamist group moved Egypt one step closer to a long-anticipated confrontation between the ruling generals and the Islamist-dominated Parliament.

headline.seo: Muslim Brotherhood Demands Military Cede Power
headline.main: Muslim Brotherhood Demands Military Cede Power in Egypt
headline.print_headline: Muslim Brotherhood Demands Egyptian Military Relinquish Power Early
